Here's the ViewModel using **CommunityToolkit.Mvvm** (recommended) and a matching XAML page with compiled bindings:

**ViewModel:**

```csharp
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.ComponentModel;
using CommunityToolkit.Mvvm.Input;

namespace MyApp.ViewModels;

public partial class ProductDetailViewModel : ObservableObject
{
    [ObservableProperty]
    private string _name = string.Empty;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private decimal _price;

    [ObservableProperty]
    private bool _isAvailable;

    [RelayCommand]
    private async Task LoadAsync()
    {
        // Simulate async data fetch
        var product = await FetchProductAsync();
        Name = product.Name;
        Price = product.Price;
        IsAvailable = product.IsAvailable;
    }

    private async Task<(string Name, decimal Price, bool IsAvailable)> FetchProductAsync()
    {
        await Task.Delay(500); // Replace with real service call
        return ("Widget Pro", 29.99m, true);
    }
}
```

The source generator creates public `Name`, `Price`, `IsAvailable` properties (with `PropertyChanged` calls) and a `LoadCommand` — all automatically.

**XAML page with compiled bindings:**

```xml
<ContentPage xmlns="http://schemas.microsoft.com/dotnet/2021/maui"
             xmlns:x="http://schemas.microsoft.com/winfx/2009/xaml"
             xmlns:vm="clr-namespace:MyApp.ViewModels"
             x:DataType="vm:ProductDetailViewModel"
             x:Class="MyApp.Views.ProductDetailPage">

    <VerticalStackLayout Padding="20" Spacing="12">
        <Label Text="{Binding Name}" FontSize="24" />
        <Label Text="{Binding Price, StringFormat='Price: {0:C2}'}" />
        <Label Text="{Binding IsAvailable, StringFormat='Available: {0}'}" />
        <Button Text="Load Product" Command="{Binding LoadCommand}" />
        <ActivityIndicator IsRunning="{Binding LoadCommand.IsRunning}" />
    </VerticalStackLayout>
</ContentPage>
```

**Key points:**

- `x:DataType` at the page root enables **compiled bindings** (8–20× faster, AOT-safe).
- `[ObservableProperty]` generates the property + `PropertyChanged` raise — no boilerplate.
- `[RelayCommand]` generates `LoadCommand` from `LoadAsync`, including `IsRunning` for free.
- `LoadCommand.IsRunning` drives the `ActivityIndicator` automatically during the async call.
- Set `BindingContext` via DI in code-behind: `public ProductDetailPage(ProductDetailViewModel vm) { InitializeComponent(); BindingContext = vm; }`

Add `XC0022` and `XC0025` as errors in your `.csproj` to catch binding mistakes at build time:

```xml
<WarningsAsErrors>XC0022;XC0025</WarningsAsErrors>
```
